{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at a local module handoff (diff parser -> review-input builder). A unit test of only parsing logic can miss wiring bugs where full files are still passed downstream. Rejected System because behavior text does not require real network/OS/subprocess; rejected Agentic because it tests input scoping, not model judgment.","test_description":"Run the diff-fetch/parsing module and input-construction module together with fixture PR patches containing unchanged sensitive lines; assert payload sent to analyzer contains only changed hunks/lines.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on real PR diff-position semantics in the external API/UI boundary. Mocked API responses can hide mapping errors (side/position/line translation) that only fail against a real PR.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions, then fetch review comments from the platform API and verify each comment appears on the intended changed line/hunk in the diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior is about model detection quality; deterministic stubs always pass and cannot validate real defect identification. Rejected Workflow because this behavior requires one model judgment, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Use a real PR fixture with a seeded known bug and run live model analysis; pass if at least one finding correctly flags the seeded defect category/location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module state consistency (inline-post results -> summary assembler) and can fail even if each function works alone. Rejected System because an in-process fake comment-poster returning IDs can reproduce the failure; rejected Agentic because no model-output quality claim is involved.","test_description":"Execute posting pipeline with stubbed inline post responses (unique IDs) and summary generation in one run context; assert every summary entry references an ID emitted in that same run and no foreign/stale IDs appear.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure occurs in local pipeline handoff/aggregation across components, not single-function logic alone. Rejected System because drop bugs are reproducible with in-process wiring and faked poster; rejected Agentic because behavior is completeness of transport, not model judgment.","test_description":"Feed multiple inline findings through orchestrator -> summary payload builder using a fake post endpoint; assert payload cardinality and IDs exactly match produced inline findings (set equality).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires a real pull request and real API operations across sequence steps. In-process fakes can hide auth, API contract, ordering, and side-effect failures.","test_description":"Run end-to-end against a real test PR with fixed findings (no model call): fetch diff via real API, post inline comments, post summary; assert all API calls succeed and resulting artifacts exist on the PR.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agent pipeline with real model generation plus downstream action stages; failures can emerge from cross-stage handoff and sequencing under live conditions. Rejected pure Agentic because behavior text requires end-to-end completion through posting stages on a real PR, not only model output correctness.","test_description":"Execute full live pipeline on a real test PR: read diff, call real model to generate findings, post inline comments, then post summary; verify completion status, non-empty coherent outputs, and no human edits/retries required.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.01,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.72}}]}
